HEADWORD: connotational
<hw>connotational</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>Having the power of implying
or suggesting something in addition to what is explicit. Contrasted with
<contr>denotative</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> connotative of (predicate).</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

